I hope we'll see this unit gain next time NCT makes a comeback because they hit me so hard I can't get over them. I also loved that the composers mentioned writing and submitting this song in record time, and sometimes that's how excellence is created: just going with the motions, not overthinking anything, and seeing where it takes you. This resulted in this funny, cheesy, cool and simply unforgettable song.

author: @NeonicBunny
text: These archiving videos/track videos bug me. Don't get me wrong, it's good that these songs get something at all when SM really didn't have to, and it encourages fans to listen to the full song. But honestly, would it have been that hard to just put the clips together for the extra 40 seconds and make it a full MV, even if it's a b-side? This doesn't just go for NCT, but for several of their artists. I mean they would have filmed footage for the whole song anyway and they already spent all the money on the sets, special effects, and choreography etc. why not put it *all* to good use?

author: @ioytuyggjtui
text:
) The Stop the CCP’s Live Organ Harvesting Poster Exhibition kicked off at the Higashi-hiroshima City Museum of Art in Hiroshima Prefecture, Japan, on July 25, 2023. The exhibition, hosted by the SMG Network (Stop Medical Genocide--Society for the Study of Organ Transplantation in China) exposes the Chinese Communist Party’s (CCP) live organ harvesting from Falun Dafa practitioners. Assemblymen and members of the House of Representatives (National Diet) attended and delivered speeches to open the event. They said they hoped more people would learn about these egregious human rights abuses and work together to end them.

The Stop the CCP’s Live Organ Harvesting Poster Exhibition kicked off at the Higashi-hiroshima City Museum of Art in Hiroshima Prefecture, Japan, on July 25, 2023.

Congressman Ishibashi Rintaro (left), Member of Hiroshima Prefecture Assembly Mr. Takehara Tetsu (middle), and Member of Higashi-hiroshima City Assembly Mr. Ochiumi Naoya (right) delivered speeches at the opening ceremony.
Dignitaries Condemn the CCP’s Forced Organ Harvesting

During the opening ceremony, Ishibashi Rintaro, a member of the House of Representatives of the National Assembly and the deputy representative of the All-Japan Local Assembly of the SMG Network (Stop Medical Genocide--Society for the Study of Organ Transplantation in China), delivered an opening speech as the sponsor of the exhibition. 

Mr. Ishibashi said that the purpose of this poster exhibition was to stop the ongoing organ harvesting and transplantation crimes in China. He said the primary victims are Falun Dafa practitioners, Uyghurs, Tibetans and other groups. The CCP treats them like criminals, and harvest their organs while they are alive.

“We SMG will never allow such a thing to happen,” said Mr. Ishibashi. “But the problem at present is that although the CCP’s human rights violations have become a matter of great concern, in Japan, many people still don’t have enough opportunities to know. This poster exhibition is of fundamental significance, and lets many Japanese understand the facts of live organ harvesting (by the CCP).”

He said that another purpose was to urge the Japanese government to enact laws on overseas transplants as soon as possible. It was also important to raise awareness of this issue in the medical community and the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare.

Councilor Takehara Tetsu, member of Hiroshima Prefecture Assembly, said in his speech, that he would share the truth with everyone. “After viewing these artworks, my heart is very heavy, and I am more aware of our great responsibility. I think this is an opportunity for me to feel the weight of my responsibility, and I feel this from these works today,” Mr. Takehara said.

Councilor Ochiumi Naoya, member of Higashi-hiroshima City Assembly, said in his speech that he was shocked when he saw the wound represented by the currency symbol on the poster, “As a Japanese, I didn’t know about this (that the CCP harvests organs from living Falun Dafa practitioners). I hope that through the poster exhibition, more people will know about this matter.”

author: @Lonnloven
text:
Only NCT could take a goofy song about Batman riding in his Batmobile at night and make it such a bop! The MV is so sexy, with the guys going into the secret lair like a bunch of superheroes or supervillains (kinda leaning toward them being villains in this MV, planning together to take down The Bat). 

I love that in this song, we got Jisung's incredible deep baritone, then Jeno's impactful rap contrasted with Hendery's more melodic rap, Johnny's sexy whispering and incredible presence, and then to top it off we get Yuta, Taeil  and Jungwoo's honey-dripping voices harmonising! If only we'd gotten Tail's presence as well… But good on the rest of the guys for covering for him!

author: @giddygerty
text:
Yo!!!! I'm loving this group. Song fits them perfectly! I want more!
1. Yuta - Oh my gosh! Longer Yuta lines...Yes! After Jungwoo's soft voice, Yuta goes 🎶 Ooohhhooohhh 🎶and gives us that solid vocals of his. YESSSSS! 
2. Jungwoo - his beautiful soft voice wraps everything hard that came before his lines 
3. Taeil - blending with Jungwoo and Yuta... so good to the ears. They should have more of this combo. The harmony is well mixed.
(Edit: I did miss it initially and I'm sorry Taeil fans 🙏 Got too shocked on Yuta lines.)
4. Hendery - I really love the way he raps. The way he enunciates the words, his tone... Aahhh so good.
5. Jisung - oh how much our little Jisungie has grown just like how his voice has matured. That deep sound he creates adds spice to the song
6. Jeno - his tone when he raps is a good contrast to the sound of Hendery and Jisung
7. Johnny - the way he delivers those English words, the way he sounds, imo, levels up that part he had with Jeno.

author: @moomoo4357
text:
It’s my song. I feel it flowing through my veins. The fist time I heard this Sogn was on August 27th, 2023. At the time, I didn’t know that the course of my life was about to change. But it did. The BAT has taken over my life. Seeing Park Jisung, the man of my dreams, singing while holding his mic in such a magnificent way has changed the structure of my brain. This song means the world to me. Nobody understands The BAT like I do. It brings something out from deep within me, an alternative persona perhaps. I go feral. It isn’t like any other song I’ve ever heard. It makes me feel special inside. This song will forever remain on repeat.  When the members sing in such a pristine and refined manner, I can’t help but go insane. It has awoken a beast inside of me.  Now that I have been enlightened by this music, I understand the meaning of life. Not only do I know the meaning of life, but I now understand the universe. Why are we here, why do things happen how they do? The answer is: because Park Jisung made me go feral during The BAT archiving video.   As of recent, men have been under a lot of fire, for being male. Regardless of my stance, I now know one thing. A man will never truly be enough. Because no man will ever be like Park Jisung. No man will ever sing The BAT to me like Park Jisung has. I will never be serenaded like that in real life. My ears will never be blessed by his presence. 
I don’t know when I will revert to my typically self, and become normal again. But I hope that day never comes. The BAT archiving video is infused in my veins. My neurons only understand The BAT. 
So maybe I sound crazy, delusional, or insane… but none of that truly matters to me. I don’t care what people think, because I only care about The BAT. 
I am the #1 The BAT listener. This isn’t an opinion. It’s a fact.
Nobody can compete with me. Nobody feels this song like I feel it. The BAT is mine. When I die, The BAT dies. Our souls are intertwined. 
I love The BAT.

text: Every time there’s a new song with jeno in it I AM ALWAYS SURPRISED to see his improvements, they just had ISTJ and he was so amazing all through-out the album and wow, he showed another NEW SIDE of him just after A MONTH? When ‘the bat’ was revealed last nct nation concert, jeno already got me on his ‘inhale exhale’ part IT WAS SO ATTRACTIVE AND CATCHY, his dance fitted the song so much my eyes were just following him and imagine how shocked I was when he started rapping so fast and he freaking ACED THAT RAP PART SO MUCH that I had to immediately look for a fancam on twitter just to double check if he really was the one who did it!!! And indeed it was him!!
